    <title>Peacebuilding contributor: Lilla Schumicky-Logan</title>
    <description>Lilla Schumicky-Logan holds MA diplomas in both philosophy and cultural anthropology and is currently a PhD candidate at the Peace Studies Department of the University of Bradford. She currently works with the Global Community Engagement and Resilience Fund (GCERF) on preventing violent extremism in South East Asia and the Middle East/North Africa region. Her areas of expertise include integration and rehabilitation of at-risk youth.
 
 
</description>
